children.value:
When set to true, the joint connections of each part, and the states of
their underlying primitive components are visualized as a spanning tree.

There are several visualizations made available when this property is set
to true:
Root Primitive of a Mechanism that is currently anchored, or connected to an anchored primitive. See
Root Primitive of a Mechanism that is free to be physically simulated.
Root Primitive of a Mechanism that has moving components.
Connection between two Primitives that share the same Assembly and Clump.
Connection between two Primitives that share the same Assembly.
